&lt;p&gt;It works after adding it to your gatsby-config.js file,
but I was just a bit disappointed by the default themes available. I like the one-monokai theme for VSCode. I wanted to use it for my code snippets on the blog. This was made possible thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/konnyakuxzy/prism-one-monokai/blob/master/prism-one-monokai.css&quot;&gt;@konnyakuxzy&lt;/a&gt; . just copy it in theme folder and require it in browser.js
voila ‚ö°&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Start a blog in 15 min.]]></title><description><![CDATA[How to start a blog in 15 min Start with cloning the gatsby gatsby-starter-blog Template üôà we got the template the next question is where‚Ä¶]]></description><link>http://blog.antonyjmalakkaran.codes/start-blog/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.antonyjmalakkaran.codes/start-blog/</guid><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2020 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;How to start a blog in 15 min&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start with cloning the gatsby gatsby-starter-blog Template üôà&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;git&lt;/span&gt; clone https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby-starter-blog.git&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;we got the template the next question is where to host, as hosting can be expensive and we are looking at a ~100-page static website. there is no need for hosting, here is where GitHub pages come to the rescue üî•.
we will go in steps from now:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make a Github repo named username.github.io (this will be your domain) üåè&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Then make a remote with this repo from the cloned directory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The tricky üé© part is that GitHub only allows the master branch to launch the site (which means gh-page package won‚Äôt work üò¢)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But worry not I have found a work around, Initialize git in the public directory in the cloned repo, If public directory not found run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;gatsby build&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and then&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token builtin class-name&quot;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; public &lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;git&lt;/span&gt; init&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add this to ‚Äúscripts‚Äù in package.json file. so that you can deploy changes with a single command &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;npm run masterdeploy&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;js&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-js&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-js&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;&quot;masterdeploy&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token operator&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;token template-string&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token string&quot;&gt;gatsby build &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cd public &amp;amp;&amp;amp; git add . 
&amp;amp;&amp;amp; git commit -m &apos;default&apos; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; git push origin master&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token template-punctuation string&quot;&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make necessary changes to the repo to make it your own.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;run this in terminal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;shell&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-shell&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;token function&quot;&gt;npm&lt;/span&gt; run masterdeploy&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There is no step 8, You are all done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy blogging üòÉ &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
