&lt;p&gt;I‚Äôm sure I‚Äôll write a lot more interesting things in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I like to thank Kiran Anto, my senior in college who gave me the motivation to do so.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This Blog aims to Record all the small achievements of the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As in the book, Atomic Habits says Small changes compound to Big differences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If You want to check out the book try Pdf-Drive&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pdfdrive.com/&quot;&gt;Pdf Drive&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quotes from Atomic Habits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You do not rise to the level of your goals. You fall to the level of your systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We often dismiss small changes because they don‚Äôt seem to matter very much at the moment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time magnifies the margin between success and failure. It will multiply whatever you feed it.  Good habits make time your ally. Bad habits make time your enemy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Decide the type of person you want to be. Prove it to yourself with small wins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It‚Äôs only by making the fundamentals of life easier that you can create the mental space needed for free-thinking and creativity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Before we can effectively build new habits, we need to get a handle on our current ones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize before you optimize. You can‚Äôt improve a habit that doesn‚Äôt exist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
